027/**
028 * Serializes POJO metamodels to HTML.
029 *
030 * <h5 class='topic'>Media types</h5>
031 *
032 * Handles <c>Accept</c> types:  <bc>text/html+schema</bc>
033 * <p>
034 * Produces <c>Content-Type</c> types:  <bc>text/html</bc>
035 *
036 * <h5 class='topic'>Description</h5>
037 *
038 * Essentially the same as {@link HtmlDocSerializer}, except serializes the POJO metamodel instead of the model itself.
039 *
040 * <p>
041 * Produces output that describes the POJO metamodel similar to an XML schema document.
042 *
043 * <p>
044 * The easiest way to create instances of this class is through the {@link HtmlSerializer#getSchemaSerializer()},
045 * which will create a schema serializer with the same settings as the originating serializer.
046 *
047 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
048 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
049 * </ul>
050 *
051 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
052 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/HtmlBasics">HTML Basics</a>
053
054 * </ul>
055 */
056public final class HtmlSchemaDocSerializer extends HtmlDocSerializer {
057
058   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
059   // Static
060   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
061
062   /**
063    * Creates a new builder for this object.
064    *
065    * @return A new builder.
066    */
067   public static Builder create() {
068      return new Builder();
069   }
070
071   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
072   // Builder
073   //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
074
075   /**
076    * Builder class.
077    */
078   @FluentSetters
079   public static class Builder extends HtmlDocSerializer.Builder {
080
081      JsonSchemaGenerator.Builder generatorBuilder;
082
083      /**
084       * Constructor, default settings.
085       */
086      protected Builder() {
087         produces("text/html");
088         accept("text/html+schema");
089         generatorBuilder = JsonSchemaGenerator.create().beanContext(beanContext());
090      }
091
092      /**
093       * Copy constructor.
094       *
095       * @param copyFrom The bean to copy from.
096       */
097      protected Builder(HtmlSchemaDocSerializer copyFrom) {
098         super(copyFrom);
099         generatorBuilder = copyFrom.generator.copy().beanContext(beanContext());
100      }
101
102      /**
103       * Copy constructor.
104       *
105       * @param copyFrom The builder to copy from.
106       */
107      protected Builder(Builder copyFrom) {
108         super(copyFrom);
109         generatorBuilder = copyFrom.generatorBuilder.copy().beanContext(beanContext());
110      }
111
112      @Override /* Context.Builder */
113      public Builder copy() {
114         return new Builder(this);
115      }
116
117      @Override /* Context.Builder */
118      public HtmlSchemaDocSerializer build() {
119         return build(HtmlSchemaDocSerializer.class);
120      }

141       * @return This object.

164       * </ul>
